<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="370" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1399,2038]" pageId="13" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1543,1569]" pageId="13" pageNumber="370">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This new species is superficially similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Park, 2020" authorityName="Park" authorityYear="2020" box="[801,1040,1543,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Dragmatucha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pedalis">
<emphasis box="[801,915,1543,1569]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="370">D. pedalis</emphasis>
Park, 2020
</taxonomicName>
which was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1342,1432,1543,1569]" name="Uganda" pageId="13" pageNumber="370">Uganda</collectingCountry>
, but can be distinguished by the slightly zigzagged antemedian band (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Park" authorityYear="2020" box="[984,1102,1579,1605]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Dragmatucha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pedalis">
<emphasis box="[984,1102,1579,1605]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="370">D. pedalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the band is nearly straight); postmedian band triangularly broadened at costa, convex medially and strongly bent inwardly, with sharp angle on CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[204,212,1670,1684]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="370">2</subScript>
(simply oblique inwardly in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Park" authorityYear="2020" box="[538,653,1651,1677]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Dragmatucha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pedalis">
<emphasis box="[538,653,1651,1677]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="370">D. pedalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="371" pageId="13" pageNumber="370" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1399,2038]" lastBlockId="14.[151,1437,151,609]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="371" pageId="13" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1687,1713]" pageId="13" pageNumber="370">Description.</emphasis>
Female (
<figureCitation box="[449,585,1687,1714]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1971,1995]" captionTargetBox="[160,1419,652,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-191@14.[151,1436,633,1947]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Dragmatucha mediolinea Park &amp; Karisch, sp. nov.: A, Adult, holotype; A1, Label; A2, Labial palpus; B, Female genitalia, GU-3889/Karisch; C, Abdomen, in SDEI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810530" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810530/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="370">Fig. 10A, A</figureCitation>
<figureCitation box="[585,600,1688,1714]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1836,1860]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,600,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-247@2.[151,1436,597,1813]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. A: View from Mt. Tonkoui over the anthropogenic influenced tropical rain forest on the slopes (by T. Karisch, 25 viii 1997); B: Collecting site for light trapping with altimontane rain forest fragments at the South-Eastern slopes of Mt. Tonkoui (by T. Karisch, 25 viii 1997; C: Fragmentary secondary rain forest south of Gouédié (by T. Karisch, 20 viii 1997); D: Collecting site at the Southern border of Gouédié (by T. Karisch, 17 viii 1997)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810510/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="370">2</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 
<quantity box="[738,841,1687,1714]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" pageId="13" pageNumber="370" unit="mm" value="12.5">12.5 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[852,913,1687,1713]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="370">Head</emphasis>
: Antenna slightly shorter than forewing; scape elongated, broadened distally, dark brown dorsally, whitish ventrally; flagellum yellowish white, pale yellowish in distal half, finely ciliate. Second palpomere of labial palpus thickened, slightly arched, orange white on outer surface, fuscous dorsally; 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[421,435,1795,1809]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="370">rd</superScript>
palpomere slender, strongly upturned, shorter than 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1021,1037,1795,1809]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="370">nd</superScript>
palpomere, orange white, brownish dorsally and ventrally. 
<emphasis box="[409,490,1831,1857]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="370">Thorax</emphasis>
: White, soot brown dorsally. Hind tibia dark brown, with long, soot-brown piliform scales medially before median spurs followed by creamy-white band, with soot-brown scales apically; spurs whitish, more brownish tinged in basal half. Forewing ground color dark brown; antemedian band narrow, yellowish white, zigzagged, triangularly broadened toward costa, convex medially and strongly bent inwardly, then sharply angled on CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[328,336,1994,2008]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="370">2</subScript>
, terminated at inner margin; submarginal band very narrow, whitish, slightly zigzagged; costa slightly arched; apex obtuse; termen sinuate; fringe dark brown, with a yellowish-white basal line. Hind wing grayish brown, with yellowish-white submarginal line, arising from near apex and terminated at M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1214,1222,169,183]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="371">2</subScript>
; apex more or less acute; termen slightly sinuate; fringe concolorous, with a narrow whitish basal line.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,609]" box="[199,1264,223,249]" pageId="14" pageNumber="371">
<emphasis box="[199,305,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="371">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[320,424,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1971,1995]" captionTargetBox="[160,1419,652,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-191@14.[151,1436,633,1947]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Dragmatucha mediolinea Park &amp; Karisch, sp. nov.: A, Adult, holotype; A1, Label; A2, Labial palpus; B, Female genitalia, GU-3889/Karisch; C, Abdomen, in SDEI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810530" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810530/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="371">Fig. 10C</figureCitation>
): Dark brown dorsally. Spinous zones weakly developed on dorsal surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="14" pageNumber="371">
<emphasis box="[199,391,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="371">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[408,512,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1971,1995]" captionTargetBox="[160,1419,652,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-191@14.[151,1436,633,1947]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Dragmatucha mediolinea Park &amp; Karisch, sp. nov.: A, Adult, holotype; A1, Label; A2, Labial palpus; B, Female genitalia, GU-3889/Karisch; C, Abdomen, in SDEI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810530" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810530/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="371">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
): Abdominal sternite VIII broadly emarginated with subovate lateral lobs bearing dense setae. Apophyses anteriores about 3/5 the length of apophyses posteriores. Ostium bursae concave. Antrum jar-shaped with convex lateral margins, weakly sclerotized, shortened, about 1/10 the length of ductus bursae. Ductus bursae broader, long, with sparsely conical spines than antrum, more than 4 times the length of corpus bursae. Corpus bursae large, ovate; signum large, elliptical, transversally elongated, with broad median groove between upper and lower plates, nearly symmetrical, with dense short conical spines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,609]" box="[199,376,475,501]" pageId="14" pageNumber="371">Male unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,729,510,537]" pageId="14" pageNumber="371" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,609]" box="[199,729,510,537]" pageId="14" pageNumber="371">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,510,536]" pageId="14" pageNumber="371">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,491,511,537]" name="Ivory Coast" pageId="14" pageNumber="371">Ivory Coast</collectingCountry>
(Montagne District).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="371" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="14" pageNumber="371">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,547,573]" pageId="14" pageNumber="371">Etymology</emphasis>
. Derived from the Latin, 
<emphasis box="[615,694,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="371">medius</emphasis>
(= middle) and linea (= line, band), referring to the linear antemedian line on the forewing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
